He lived mostly in the Greek settlements of lower Italy, where his school existed for some centuries after his death. — De- mocritum: of Abdera, one of the originators of the theory of atoms; said to have lived from 460 to 361 or 357 B.C. — Xenocraten: after Plato, Speusippus was the first head of the Academic School; Xenocrates succeeded him. He lived from 397 to 315 or 313. — Zenonem : of Citium in CypruS, founder of Stoicism, born about 357 , is said to have lived to the age of 98. — Cleanthen: he followed Zeno in the presidency of the Stoic school. His age at death is vari- ously given as 99 and as 80 years. —·—· quern vidistis: see Introd.
